OL,6,FAt the original sentencing hearing
OL,7,Fbarrister Robin Rouch, for Boland,
OL,8,Fsaid once the payment arrangements had
OL,9,Fbeen set up they continued monthly
OL,10,Fwith "little involvement" by the
OL,11,Fdefendant, and once the payments were
OL,12,Fdetected they were always going to be
OL,13,Ftraced back to the defendant.
OL,15,FMr Rouch said immediate custody would
OL,16,Fhave a significant impact on the
OL,17,Fdefendant's daughter, including the
OL,18,Flikely loss of the family home, but he
OL,19,Fsaid it was accepted the situation was
OL,20,Fone of Boland's own making.
